Practice:
---------

Read a path and Check if given path is a file or a directory

path_file_dir.py
---------------

import os
path=input("Enter your path: ")
if os.path.isfile(path):
	print(f'The given path: {path} is a file')
else:
	print(f'The given path: {path} is directory')

Enter your path: /home/santhosh
/home/santhosh is directory

Enter your path: c:\\Users\santhosh
c:\\Users\santhosh is directory

path_file_dir.py
---------------

import os
path=input("Enter your path: ")

if os.path.exists(path):
	print(f'Given path: {path} is a valid path')
else:
	print(f'Given path: {path} is not exisitng on this host')

Enter your path: x:
Given path: x: is not existing on this host

Enter your path: /home/santhosh/test.py
Given path: /home/santhosh/test.py is not existing on this host


path_file_dir.py
----------------

import os
path=input("Enter your path: ")

if os.path.exists(path):
	print(f'Given path: {path} is a valid path')
		if os.path.isfile(path):
			print(f'The given path: {path} is a file')
		else:
			print(f'The given path: {path} is directory')
else:
	print(f'Given path: {path} is not exisitng on this host')

Enter your path: /home/santhosh/test.py
Given path: /home/santhosh/test.py is a valid path
and it is a file 

#This is a platform independet script(you can run on any operating system)
import os
path=input("Enter your path: ")

if os.path.exists(path):
	print(f"Given path : {path}is a valid path")
	if os.path.isfile(path):
		print("and it is a file path")
	else:
		print("and it is a directory path")
else:
	print(f"Given path : {path} is not existing on this host")





